## Output Quality Requirements

Your final summary MUST include:
- **Source citations**: For every fact, cite where you found it — chapter name,
  section ID (e.g. "page-734"), or reference node name.
- **Exact syntax**: When documenting commands, keywords, or input file format,
  give verbatim code examples. Use backtick inline code for keywords, and
  fenced code blocks for multi-line examples.
- **Gotchas and caveats**: Explicitly note any non-obvious rules, formatting
  requirements, or common pitfalls (e.g. "Gaussian requires a blank line after
  the geometry section", "Psi4 expects units in Bohr, not Angstrom").
- **Brevity**: Be concise. The parent agent needs actionable details, not
  tutorials. Skip background exposition — assume the parent knows the domain.
